company_updates_collection.description:
Will the war in Ukraine lead to world hunger and a shortage of semiconductors? How to avoid it?

The answer lies in improving supply chains with end-to-end visibility solutions. What helpful data points are available with real-time cargo tracking and how will they help?

Read our CEO Alexa Sinyachova's article on HackerNoon and learn about it.

#supplychain #visibility #data

Let's create a smart container in 2 minutes! And increase revenue from 5 to 10 percent per container by providing a smart container-monitoring service.

We proud to announce new Moeco container monitoring solution. Track location, temperature, light, humidity and shock in real time.

Now available and covering more than 180 countries, Moeco’s container monitoring solution also helps operators comply with Smart Container initiatives.

Finally — the tracker is designed to operate for 10 years without maintenance.

Read more in Container Management. 

#supplychain #containermonitoring #container #visibility

Do we want to promote sustainability? Definitely yes!

Logistics is still one of the most harmful areas for the environment. Our goal is to help logistics companies become more sustainable.

Discussed with Stacey Higginbotham how tracking down to the box level would make logistics more sustainable and user-friendly.

#logistics #sustainability #staceyoniot #supplychain #moeco

Let's see you at our booth in the Discovery Zone at Breakbulk Europe 2022!

And don't miss Alexa Sinyachova presentation at Women in Breakbulk Breakfast. It will take place on May 18 at The Floyd restaurant.

See you ;)

#breakbulk #supplychain #rotterdam

At Moeco we believe that end-to-end supply chain analytics is about helping people. Reduce delivery time, reduce cost and rest assured that everything is fine with the shipment.

This is exactly what we needed to help deliver humanitarian aid to Ukraine. Our CEO Alexa Sinyachova told Breakbulk Events & Media how IoT technology helps where it's needed.

Read the interview at the link. 

#supplychain #iot #analytics #ukraine

The Register: Meet Moeco, Ukrainian-led biz using IoT trackers to follow supplies into invaded land.

A breathtaking story about how humanity and technology win in the fight for the lives of Ukrainians.

Brilliant text from Brandon Vigliarolo, who spoke with our CEO Alexa Sinyachova. 

#supplychain #iot #technology #ukraine

Being sustainable is profitable. We wrote an article in VentureBeat on how reducing CO2 emissions in the #supplychain leads to lower labor expenses and less risk in transportation.

Read the secret to achieving sustainability in your supply chain here:

#sustainability #supplychain

On this week we enjoyed visited #TheGarageDisrupt in sunny Riyadh and told about end-to-end supply chain analytics. 

#supplychain #analytics #moecoacttracker
Watch Moeco Intro Video and learn more about our solutions!

How long does it take to install Moeco trackers?

When it comes to putting tracking devices on containers, the usual way takes a lot of time. Think of a big GPS tracker, about as big as 3-4 iPhones stacked up, needing bolts and screws to attach it and take it off. Imagine this – you need to track 10,000 containers or pallets every year. That means about 500 hours just spent on putting on and taking off these devices. That's half a year's work just doing this one boring job.

But what if you have even more containers? Like 500,000 a year. This job gets really big, needing a whole team just for this repetitive task.

Now, here's what Moeco offers: it's a simple sticker. Peel it off, stick it on, and you're all set in 5 seconds. That's right – only 5 seconds for each container, not the 3 minutes the typical way takes.

This isn't just saving time; it's a big jump in how efficiently you use your resources. Moeco is not just about tracking things; we're about making it super easy to fit into your logistics work.

#supplychain #supplychainsolutions #logisticssolutions

What transport modes do Moeco's sensors support? To put it simply, there isn't one we don't cover. 

Our sensors attach to containers or pallets, collecting real-time data on location, temperature, humidity, shocks, and light during land transport, be it via truck or rail.

At sea or in the air, they switch roles to data loggers, storing crucial information until they can reconnect to our platform to upload it. Despite the limited cell service over oceans or the strict rules for communication in air transport, they continue to record every critical aspect. As soon as they can reconnect, the complete data set is promptly transmitted to Moeco's platform.

Discover more on our website https://www.moeco.io/ or reach out here on LinkedIn.
